109 being retained by the school district.
110 10. (1) Beginning in the 2027-28 school year and continuing in all subsequent
111 school years, if a student has a substantial reading deficiency at the end of third grade, the
112 student's parent or guardian and appropriate school staff shall discuss whether the student
113 should be retained in grade level, based on a consideration of all relevant factors, including
114 the reading deficiency, the student's progress in other subject areas, and the student's overall
115 intellectual, physical, emotional, and social development.
116 (2) A decision to [promote or] retain a student with a substantial reading deficiency at
117 the end of grade three shall be made only after direct personal consultation with the student's
118 parent or guardian and after the formulation of a specific plan of action to remedy the
119 student's reading deficiency as determined by the department of elementary and
120 secondary education.
121 (3) Based on such student's performance on the reading screener at the end of
122 the third grade, the student shall be retained in grade three unless:
123 (a) Such student scores "approaching expectations" or higher on a retest
124 opportunity through the Missouri reading screener after successfully completing a state-
125 approved summer reading program; or
126 (b) Such student qualifies for a good cause exemption under subsection 11 of this
